which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2017-12-20T21:28:19Z", "updated_at": "2018-10-11T17:26:15Z", "closed_at": "2018-10-11T17:26:15Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The weak reference is never non-null because Rust linkage is used for the function:\r\n\r\n```\r\n#[cfg(target_os = \"linux\")]\r\n#[allow(deprecated)]\r\nfn min_stack_size(attr: *const libc::pthread_attr_t) -> usize {\r\n    weak!(fn __pthread_get_minstack(*const libc::pthread_attr_t) -> libc::size_t);\r\n\r\n    match __pthread_get_minstack.get() {\r\n        None => libc::PTHREAD_STACK_MIN,\r\n        Some(f) => unsafe { f(attr) },\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nApparently, this problem was introduced in commit 1a31e1c09f89daeefa06ca9336912e9bcadb0c1d.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, `__pthread_get_minstack` is an internal glibc symbol without any ABI stability. `PTHREAD_STACK_MIN` is really, really tight (particularly on x86-64 with AVX-512), and the constant probably does not mean what you think it does.", "closed_by": {"login": "fweimer", "id": 2729073, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI3MjkwNzM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2729073?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/fweimer", "html_url": "https://github.com/fweimer", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fweimer/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fweimer/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fweimer/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fweimer/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fweimer/subscriptions", "orga